    <section id="about">
        <h2>About P. Diddy</h2>
        <p>Sean Combs, known professionally as P. Diddy (formerly Puff Daddy), is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, record producer, and entrepreneur. He was born on November 4, 1969, in New York City. Diddy is known for his influence on hip-hop and R&B music, as well as for his ventures in fashion and business.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="career">
        <h2>Career</h2>
        <p>P. Diddy began his career in the early 1990s as a talent director at Uptown Records. He later founded Bad Boy Records, where he produced and promoted numerous hit records. He gained fame with his debut album "No Way Out" in 1997, which featured the smash hit "I'll Be Missing You."</p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="achievements">
        <h2>Achievements</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Three Grammy Awards, including Best Rap Album for "No Way Out."</li>
            <li>Billboard Music Awards for Top R&B/Hip-Hop Album.</li>
            <li>Forbes listed him as one of the richest artists in the world, with a net worth in the hundreds of millions.</li>
            <li>Founder of the clothing line Sean John, which won a Council of Fashion Designers of America award.</li>
            <li>Philanthropist involved in various charitable causes, including education and disaster relief.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
